goals.question: What is the distribution of deaths for the top 10 deadliest disasters?

code:
```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Deaths', data=data, ax=ax, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of disaster deaths over time?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="Entity", y="Deaths", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of deaths by disaster type?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('Entity').mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='Entity', y='Deaths', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.axhline(y=data['Deaths'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average deaths')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    plt.title('What is the average number of deaths per disaster type?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
    ax.set(xlabel='Disaster', ylabel='Deaths')
    ax.axhline(y=data['Deaths'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Deaths')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
